    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the juice of your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>in a medium bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>herb marinade</strong></p><p>Dip the <strong>chopped basa</strong> in the <strong>herb marinade</strong> (reserve the remaining marinade)</p>",
